---
description: Non-negotiable git safety constraints for agent operations
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never commit on `develop`, `main`, or `master`.
- Never push `develop`, `main`, or `master` directly.
- Stage named files or hunks only; do not use `git add .`, `git add -A`, or `git add --all`.
- Split commits by logical scope; do not bundle unrelated workstreams.
